The paper deals with sampling from large-scale network datasets, which are often social activity streams. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a streaming graph sampling algorithm, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient processing of large-scale data, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with network domains and network systems, which are related to cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper evaluates the efficacy of the proposed method empirically, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
